A businessman, Awalu Mohammed, on Thursday appeared in a Karshi Grade I Area Court in Abuja for allegedly owing a debt of N225,000 on a cow. Mohammed, 30, residing at Nyanya in Abuja, is facing charges of criminal breach of trust, cheating and criminal misappropriation. The Prosecutor, Mr Ayotunde Adeyanju, told the court that one Bello Abubakar of Karu Abattoir in Abuja reported the matter at the Karu Police Station on May 27. “The complainant alleged that sometime in February, the defendant purchased a cow from him for N275, 0000 with an agreement to pay in few days’ time. “But with intend to cheat the complainant, the defendant sold the cow and paid only the sum of N50, 000. “The defendant dishonestly converted the remaining N225, 000 to his own personal use and absconded to an unknown destination until he was traced and arrested, “Adeyanju said. The prosecutor said that the offence contravened the provisions of Sections 312, 322 and 309 of the Penal Code. The Judge, Mr Anas Isah, admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N100, 000 with two sureties in like sum and adjourned the case until June 11, for further hearing.